UPDATED: DEC 24, 2013 Best seasonal beer ive ever had, very rich, strong, colorful beer. After one you really feel effect. Very good balance, good carbonation.


///Bottle from 1988 on 21-12-2013 Ar:7 Ap:2 Ta: 5 Pa: 2 Ov: 10 
Aroma: Caramel, apple syrup, vinegar, apricot  Appearance: Brown yeast flocks, no foam, no lace, amber on bottom, yellow on top, no see through at bottom  Taste: Apple syrup, sweet, cinnamon, plums, candy sugar  Bottle probably not very well conditioned

///Bottle 2113 - Aroma: Oranges, peach, caramel, little booze, little spicy  Appearance: Orange, amber, white head, quickly disappearing head, light lace  Taste: Oranges, caramel, peach, apricot,little booze in aftertaste, spicy aftertaste

bottle @ dulle griet , ghent
a Strong flavour of alcohol, malt and hops.
can be kept for 20 years or longer;

UPDATED: DEC 7, 2008 Pours a clear amber with a white head. Smells of alcohol and malts. Very sweet. Flavors of sweet caramel malts, yeast and alcohol. Bitter finish with alcohol. Kinda fresh, could do with some lagereing, I guess.                                     Vintage 2005
Pours a hazy amber with lots of floaties and a big hazy foamy head. &&#35;40;Was clear in the bottle but the overcabonation churned everything, I guess.&&#35;41;
Sweet with aromas of raisins and figs. Also has an alcohol touch. Full bodied with a slightly sticky mouthfeel. High carbonation. Bitter finish with a warmiong alcohol sensation..
